		shell.h
		Makefile
		README




	Compile Instructions:
	
		Enter a2 directory and type "make". This creates exe named xsh




	Operating Instructions:
		
		Run shell by doing:
			
			./xsh
		
		Shell displays a prompt using class account username

		Valid formats for input:
			
			executablefilename
			executablefilename argument
			executablefilename | executablefilename
			executablefilename | executablefilename | ...
			exit


	1 argument allowed per command


	To close --> type "exit"

	

	Design Decisions:

		- All functions stored in main.cpp:

			- shell control
			- command execution
			- input parsing
			- commmand building
			- pipeline execution

		- The USER environment variable is used to show account username in the shell prompt.
		- When a command is entered without a slash, it is searched using PATH environment variable.
		- Child processes are created with fork()
		- execvp() executes programs
		- waitpid() waits for programs to finish
		

	No known bugs yet.

	
	Lessons Learned:
		
		In this assignment, we learned how to create child processes uisng fork(),
		running/waiting for processes with execvp() and waitpid(). We also learned 
		how pipes are applied to shells using dup2(), input parsing, and input validation. 
